@YuweiXiao Hi, allow me to rephrase. This is what's actually going on in git master (removing the adapter abstraction)

```scala
df.mapPartitions { rows => 
  rows.map { row =>
    new AvroSerializer().serialize(row)
  }
}
```

there could be extra initialization cost for each invocation of `serialize` but it seems to be *recreating* the AvroSerializer for each row, which I suspect is the main culprit.

@boneanxs 
True, full support of Dataset is the long term solution. In my experiment, optimizing the usage of `AvroSerializer` could save 80% costs of the source data reading. But the optimization requires modification of the `AvroSerializer` source code in the spark side.

@qjqqyy Yes, each row will initialize `AvroSerializer` (variables in the lambda named `converter`)

> is this just for DeleteHelper consolidation ?

Contains DeleteHelper, and other Helpers, currently verifying the problem while solving the problem
@xushiyan

@alexeykudinkin  find the root cause.
we should set       sqlContext.sparkSession.sessionState.conf.setConfString("spark.sql.parquet.enableVectorizedReader", "true") for cow table. 
if we enable vectorizedReader, we can get only 10% regression
